The task is to identify the specific line item and amount that represent the decrease in amounts owed to the entity for goods or services sold or provided on credit during the period.

In a cash flow statement, "Accounts Receivable" represents amounts owed to the entity by customers. A decrease in Accounts Receivable means the entity collected cash from the amounts owed (i.e., reduction in receivables).

From the provided problem, the relevant line item is:
"(Increase) Decrease in Accounts Receivable  | -1355463.34 | 2024-01-28"

The value is -1355463.34.

This shows a decrease of 1,355,463.34 in amounts owed to the entity.

Hence, the extracted value is "-1355463.34".
